dct_title_s: Formosa, southern part, to illustrate the paper by M. Beazeley, M. Inst. C.E.
dct_description_sm: Roads, settlements, and fort and lighthouse on southern tip of island are shown. Sugar growing region in vicinity of Tan-kang [Donggang] and area inhabited by Aborigines in eastern mountains are shown. Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depth shown by soundings. Route of expedition shown in red. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 7 (1885), no. 1, pp. 1-23; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
